name: Synth Mining
description: Synth Mining solves some of the biggest roadblocks in image-based data science by combining collaborative outsourced datamining with synthetic image generation. It's built using Python, Pytorch, and Cuda.

name: Raven
description: Raven is simple dynamically-typed programming language built with Rust. The goal of the project was to experiment with different language constructs regarding design and implementations.

name: Mouseless Mouse
description: Mouseless Mouse is a glove with sensors that pick up hand movement and translate it to mouse input. It can be used to play video games or to complete any other computer tasks.

name: Leet Camp
description: LeetCamp is a learning-focused project that teaches Data Structures and Algorithms through the lens of LeetCode problems, preparing everyone to crush their technical interviews!

name: Mannequin
description: Mannequin uses AI and other parameters to fit you in a 3D model. You can try on clothes from online brands and see how clothes would fit on your personal proportions.

name: Maroon Rides
description: Maroon Rides is a project that started at ACC and has gone on to garner 10k+ downloads. It offers a seamless and efficient transportation experience for the Texas A&M University community.

name: Aggie Seek
description: AggieSeek is an application that allows you to search for and select an unlimited number of courses to track. You will get instant notifications anytime the seats or the instructors in your courses change.

name: Rev Registration
description: Rev Registration was a project that streamlined registration at Texas A&M. The project was incorporated by the university to create the registration system used by Aggies today.
